This paper is about off-policy reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new conceptual framework for off-policy learning, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves theoretical analysis and investigation of algorithms, which suggests that it may be relevant to researchers in the subfields of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), control systems (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO).
